Here's an example of how to use JavaScript to click a button with the class `svelte-57yet2`:

```javascript
var button = document.querySelector('.svelte-57yet2');
button.click();
```

In this example, `document.querySelector()` is used to find the button element with the class `svelte-57yet2`, and then the `.click()` method is called on that element to simulate a click on the button. You can use this code in combination with the `execute_script()` method in Selenium to automate clicking the button on a website from Python.

